{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894954213,"sessionID":"ses_2846be6dbffem0trR4hEIofkpE","part":{"id":"prt_d7b94405b001aN1kFrWgUqyhY2","messageID":"msg_d7b9427aa001f0l6Eef8Au7svn","sessionID":"ses_2846be6dbffem0trR4hEIofkpE","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_721610e34d564ef4a33aad75","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - list top-level directories\n2. Look for any existing test directories (test/, test/e2e/, etc.)\n3. Find any existing proposal.md files to understand the format/convention used\n4. Look at the client-go directory structure mentioned in the spec\n5. Find any existing Makefile or test scripts\n6. Look for any existing E2E test patterns or frameworks used in the project\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- Existing test infrastructure\n- Proposal format conventions (if any exist)\n- Client-go directory structure\n- Testing frameworks/patterns already in use\n- Any relevant configuration files (go.mod, Makefile, etc.)","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2846babc3ffe2RMCcknyrS9COh (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Exploration Summary\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\nThe project root is at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z` and is a **Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents** (module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`).\n\n**Top-level directories:**\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `agentd/` | Idle cleanup controller |\n| `bin/` | Compiled Go binaries (router, workloadmanager, agentd, picod) |\n| `changes/` | Change request proposals (AR-001 through AR-041), each with a `proposal.md` |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD design and spec documents |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | CLI toolkit |\n| `client-go/` | Generated Kubernetes client (clientset, informers, listers) |\n| `cmd/` | Go binary entry points (router, workloadmanager, agentd, picod, cli) |\n| `code-execution/` | Code execution module |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment configurations |\n| `docker/` | Dockerfiles (Dockerfile, Dockerfile.router, Dockerfile.picod) |\n| `example/` | Example applications (e.g., pcap-analyzer) |\n| `hack/` | Code generation scripts (`update-codegen.sh`, `boilerplate.go.txt`) |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Idle cleanup module |\n| `integrations/` | External integrations (e.g., dify-plugin) |\n| `manifests/` | Kubernetes manifests and Helm charts (`manifests/charts/base`) |\n| `pkg/` | Go library packages (agentd, apis, common, picod, router, store, workloadmanager) |\n| `python-sdk/` | Python SDK with tests |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration module |\n| `session-routing/` | Session routing module |\n| `session-store/` | Session store module |\n| `test/` | Test scripts (chart rendering, Makefile tests) |\n| `testing/` | TDD manifest document |\n\n**Key top-level files:**\n- `go.mod` / `go.sum` - Go module definition (Go 1.25.0)\n- `Makefile` - Build system\n- `proposal.md` - Current active proposal (AR-036: Dify plugin integration)\n- `project.md` - Project context document\n- `delta-spec.md` - Detailed delta spec for workloadmanager unit tests (AR-038)\n- `tasks.md` - Task tracking\n- `test_spec.md` - Test specification\n- `design.md` - Design document\n- `coverage.out` - Go coverage output\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing Test Infrastructure\n\n**Test directories and files:**\n\n| Location | Type | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| `test/chart/test_render.sh` | Bash script | Helm chart rendering tests (271 lines, 60+ assertions) |\n| `test/makefile/test_makefile.sh` | Bash script | Makefile target tests (375 lines, 25 test groups) |\n| `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | Markdown | TDD contract defining required test cases per module |\n| `pkg/*/*_test.go` | Go tests | 35+ Go test files across packages |\n| `python-sdk/tests/test_*.py` | Python tests | 7 Python test files |\n\n**Go test files found (35 total):**\n- `pkg/router/` - 8 test files (router, loadbalancer, health, errors, backend, middleware, jwt, server, config)\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/` - 6 test files (const, handler/models, handler/sandbox_lifecycle, handler/sandbox_delete, reconciler/metrics, reconciler/fixtures, response/response)\n- `pkg/picod/` - 7 test files (server, execute, sanitize, auth, health, config, files/*)\n- `pkg/store/` - 4 test files (store_valkey, store_redis, singleton, codec)\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` - 5 test files (groupversion_info, codeinterpreter_types, constants, shared_types, agent_type)\n- `pkg/agentd/` - 1 test file (reconciler_test.go)\n\n**No `test/e2e/` directory exists yet** - AR-041 is the proposal to create it, but it is currently a skeleton with TODO placeholders.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Proposal Format Conventions\n\nProposals follow a consistent structure located in `changes/AR-XXX/proposal.md`. The root `proposal.md` is the currently active proposal. The format convention is:\n\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX — Title\n\n## Purpose\n<!-- Brief description of what and why -->\n\n## Scope\n### In Scope\n<!-- Numbered list of deliverables, often with tables -->\n\n### Out of Scope\n<!-- Bullet list of explicit exclusions -->\n\n## Impact Analysis\n### Dependencies\n<!-- Table: Dependency | Source | Description -->\n\n### Affected Components\n<!-- Table: File/Directory | Status | Description -->\n\n### Risk Assessment\n<!-- Table: Risk | Level | Mitigation -->\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n### 1. Option A vs Option B (selected option marked)\n<!-- Pros, cons, decision rationale -->\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n<!-- Checkbox list of verifiable criteria -->\n\n## Status\n<!-- Checkbox list: Proposal review, Implementation, Verification -->\n```\n\n**AR-041 (E2E tests)** is a skeleton proposal with a slightly different/additional structure including:\n- `## Architecture Summary` (Current State / Target State)\n- `## Upstream Dependencies`\n- `## Test Strategy` (with test layer table, test patterns, coverage targets)\n\nThe **delta-spec.md** (AR-038) uses a more detailed Gherkin-style format with `R-N` requirement sections, each containing `Scenario` blocks with `GIVEN/WHEN/THEN` structure.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Client-Go Directory Structure\n\n```\nclient-go/\n  clientset/\n    clientset.go\n    fake.go\n    real.go\n    typed/\n      runtime/          # Typed client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API group\n    versioned/\n      clientset.go\n      fake/             # Fake clientset for testing\n      scheme/           # Scheme registration\n      typed/            # Versioned typed clients\n  informers/\n    externalversions/\n      factory.go\n      internalinterfaces/\n      runtime/          # Informers for runtime CRDs\n  listers/\n    runtime/            # Listers for runtime CRDs\n      v1alpha1/         # v1alpha1 listers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n```\n\nThe client-go is generated using `k8s.io/code-generator` via `hack/update-codegen.sh`, which runs:\n- `kube::codegen::gen_helpers` - generates deepcopy/defaults code\n- `kube::codegen::gen_client` - generates clientset, informers, listers with `--with-watch` and `--with-applyconfig`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Testing Frameworks and Patterns\n\n**Go Testing:**\n- **Framework**: Standard `testing` package\n- **Assertion library**: `github.com/stretchr/testify` (assert + require)\n- **HTTP testing**: `net/http/httptest` for HTTP handler tests\n- **Mocking**: Hand-rolled mock interfaces (e.g., `mockLoadBalancer`, `mockReconcilerStore`, `mockMetricsRecorder`, `mockAgentRuntimeLister`, `mockPodLister`)\n- **Fixtures**: Builder pattern with functional options (e.g., `newAgentRuntime(ns, name, opts...)`, `newPod(ns, name, opts...)`, `newSandboxInfo(sessionID, opts...)`)\n- **Test file naming**: `*_test.go` co-located with source files\n- **Fixtures file**: `fixtures_test.go` pattern for shared test helpers\n\n**Python Testing:**\n- **Framework**: `pytest`\n- **Test location**: `python-sdk/tests/` and `cmd/cli/tests/`\n- **Linting**: `ruff` (preferred) or `flake8` (fallback)\n\n**Bash/Shell Testing:**\n- Custom test scripts with `assert_pass`, `assert_fail`, `assert_contains`, `assert_not_contains` helper functions\n- Color-coded output (GREEN/RED/YELLOW)\n- PASS/FAIL/SKIP summary\n\n**TDD Manifest Requirements** (`testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`):\n- Test-to-Code ratio must be > 0.4 (40 lines of test per 100 lines of code)\n- Every source file must have a corresponding test file\n\n---\n\n### 6. Relevant Configuration Files\n\n**`go.mod`** (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`, Go 1.25.0):\n- Key dependencies: gin, go-redis/v9, valkey-go, golang-jwt/jwt/v5, k8s.io/client-go, controller-runtime, prometheus/client_golang, stretchr/testify\n- K8s version: v0.34.1\n\n**`Makefile`** targets:\n| Target | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `all` | build + test + lint |\n| `ci` | build + test + test-coverage + lint + helm-lint |\n| `build` | Compiles all 4 binaries (router, workloadmanager, agentd, picod) |\n| `build/<binary>` | Individual binary compilation |\n| `test` | `go test ./...` |\n| `test-coverage` | `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...` |\n| `test-chart` | Runs `test/chart/test_render.sh` |\n| `lint` | `golangci-lint run` |\n| `fmt` / `vet` | `go fmt ./...` / `go vet ./...` |\n| `docker` | Builds all 3 Docker images |\n| `helm-lint` / `helm-template` | Helm chart validation |\n| `python-lint` / `python-test` | Python linting and pytest |\n| `gen-client` | Runs `hack/update-codegen.sh` |\n\n**Note**: The GitHub workflow `e2e.yml` references `make e2e` and `make e2e-clean` targets, but these are **NOT currently defined in the Makefile**. This is a gap that AR-041 would need to address.\n\n**GitHub Workflows** (`.github/workflows/`):\n| Workflow | Trigger | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | PR to main/release-* | Build workload manager Docker image |\n| `lint.yml` | PR to main/release-* | golangci-lint (path-filtered) |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | PR/merge_group | Go test coverage with Codecov upload |\n| `e2e.yml` | PR to main/release-* | E2E tests using Kind cluster (references `make e2e`) |\n| `python-lint.yml` | PR | Python linting |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | PR | Python SDK tests |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | PR | Verify generated client-go is up to date |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Release tags | Build and push release images |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Release | Publish Dify plugin |\n| `codespell.yml` | PR | Spell checking |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | PR | Copyright header validation |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | PR | Workflow approval gating |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2846babc3ffe2RMCcknyrS9COh","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775894811705,"end":1775894954210}}}}
